sentence: U.S. stock index futures rose for a fourth straight session on Tuesday as U.S.-China officials reaffirmed their commitment to a Phase-1 trade deal, adding to market optimism from signs of progress in developing treatments and vaccines for COVID-19.
ET, Dow e-minis 1YMc1 were up 0.66% at 28,425.
S&P 500 e-minis ESc1 were up 0.42% at 3,442, while Nasdaq 100 e-minis NQc1 were up 0.10% at 11,648.
